The paper deals with the problem of multi-agent path finding, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of search-based solvers and compilation-based solvers, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Boolean satisfiability (SAT), which is a topic in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
